    "c_faq_tabs_BMtYJg": {
      "type": "c-faq-tabs",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_item_D44yQ6": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "tab_id": "medications",
            "question": "Can I get the dietary nitrates in Berkeley Life just through my diet?",
            "answer": "<p>Leafy greens, beetroot, arugula, spinach and celery are all vegetables known to be high in dietary nitrates. However, nutrient density of the soil across the country makes it difficult to predict exactly how much of these greens are required daily to provide a clinically effective dose of nitrates to produce Nitric Oxide. In our experience, it requires more leafy greens than most people over 35 are willing or able to consume every day.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "faq_item_HamWDY": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "tab_id": "medications",
            "question": "Can I take Berkeley Life with other medications?",
            "answer": "<p>Berkeley Life is safe, well-tolerated, and has no counter-indications for medications. As always, if you are uncertain work with your healthcare provider to determine the appropriate combination of medicine and supplementation that's right for you.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "faq_item_6QgJYU": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "tab_id": "medications",
            "question": "How long do I need to take Berkeley Life before I see results?",
            "answer": "<p>As with all supplements, everyone will feel a difference at different speeds. There are some who notice a difference right away, and others see benefits after using the product for about a month. However, unlike most supplements you can validate that our N.O. supplements are working by using our patented Nitric Oxide Test Strip before and 90 minutes after you take the supplement.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "faq_item_r8Q7Gg": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "tab_id": "medications",
            "question": "What are Nitric Oxide test strips and how do they work?",
            "answer": "<p>Our test strips provide a quick, simple way to measure your body’s nitric oxide levels through saliva. Just place the strip on your tongue, press the ends together, and check the color—it takes less than 10 seconds and gives real-time insight into your NO status.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "faq_item_rc4aqk": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "tab_id": "safety",
            "question": "How often should I test my Nitric Oxide levels?",
            "answer": "<p>It's up to you but we recommend using the test strips regularly to begin with to understand your baseline levels and how supplementation influences your levels. Here are some suggestions - First thing in the morning - Before and after eating a nitrate-rich meal - Before and after workouts or activity - Before and after taking Berkeley Life Nitric Oxide Foundation This helps you spot patterns and fine-tune your habits for better nitric oxide production and performance.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "faq_item_TMm7LW": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "tab_id": "safety",
            "question": "Why should I care about my Nitric Oxide levels?",
            "answer": "<p>Nitric oxide is essential for healthy blood flow, energy, brain function, and heart health. Low levels are common, especially after age 40 or with stress, poor diet, or prescription mouthwash use. Testing helps you understand when your body needs support—so you can adjust your nutrition or supplement routine.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        }
      },
